rComments: took the course in summer 2017. Lots of memorization so I recommend attending lectures to grasp the material better. We only had a midterm and a final, both were easy and he included humour into some questions which was cool

Prof Sidnell was actually a really good prof. At first lectures seem boring and dry but get more interesting over time. He has a loud voice, and included humour and sometimes memes to make class interesting. The midterm was pretty easy as long as you regularly go to class. Would take another course with him again.

Incredible teacher! Even though he goes at a breakneck pace, his lectures are really engaging and understandable, with great examples (a lot of little clips to illustrate linguistic quirks - he led the Linguistic Anthropology class).

GREAT PROF! His lectures were clear, concise and easily understandable. He played a number of funny videos throughout the course which made it easy to stay awake in class! Although he seemed a bit unenthusiastic at times, he is undoubtedly a hilarious prof and I recommend him to anyone!
